articles.author: Interesting Engineering
articles.title: Polar ice melting makes Earth ‘bulkier’ to rotate, causing longer days: Study - Interesting Engineering
articles.content: As ice melts on the Earth's surface, it slows the planet's rotation and increases the day. ETH Zurich research shows that the slowdown slightly lengthens our days—just a few milliseconds compared to the typical 86,400 seconds. In physics, there's a law called conservation of angular momentum.
